1. Initial project
Create an empty react app with typescript template
npx create-react-app my-component-sample --template typescrip
2. Add storybook, for component UI preveiw
npx sb init
3. Clean project, initial code.
Remove /public folder, cause it is not used, at last clean /src folder to be like this:
index.ts
import MyComponent from './MyComponent/MyComponent';
export { MyComponent }
MyComponent.ts
import React, { Component } from 'react';
class MyComponent extends Component {
    render() {
        return (
            <div>
                Test
            </div>
        );
    }
}export default MyComponent;
MyComponent.sories.ts
import React from 'react';
import { Story, Meta } from '@storybook/react/types-6-0';
import MyComponent from './MyComponent';
export default {
  title: 'MyComponent',
  component: MyComponent,
  argTypes: {
    backgroundColor: { control: 'color' },
  },
  args: {
    inputValue: '',
    disabled: false,
    required: false,
  },
} as Meta;
const Template: Story = (args: any) => <MyComponent {...args} />;
export const Default = Template.bind({});
Default.args = {
  primary: true,
  label: 'MyComponent',
};
4. Config Babel for building ts, tsx, scss to js
yarn add @babel/core @babel/cli @babel/preset-typescript --dev
Add babel config in the package.json
"babel": {
    "presets": [
      "@babel/preset-react",
      "@babel/preset-typescript"
    ],
    "plugins": [
      "babel-plugin-transform-scss"   //for build scss
    ]
  },
5. Config TypeScript for building .d.ts files
in tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "outDir": "build",
    "declaration": true,
    "emitDeclarationOnly": true,
    "jsx": "react-jsx",
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
  },
  "include": [
    "src"
  ],
  "exclude": [
    "**/*.stories.tsx"
  ]
}
6. Add scripts
"scripts": {
    "start": "start-storybook -p 6006 -s public",
    "build": "tsc & babel src --out-dir build --extensions \\".ts,.tsx\\" --ignore src/*/*.stories.tsx --source-maps inline",
},
7. Run the project in storybook
yarn storybook
8. Config workflow yml to publish to npmjs
Use actions publish package to npmjs
name: Node.js Package
on:
  push:
    branches:
      - master
  pull_request:
    branches:
      - master
jobs:
  publish-npm:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v2
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v2.1.5
        with: 
          node-version: 14.x
      - run: yarn install
      - run: yarn build
      - run: npm --no-git-tag-version version $(npx semver $(npm info @bryht/auto-complete version) -i)
      - uses: JS-DevTools/npm-publish@v1
        with:
          token: ${{ secrets.NPM_TOKEN }}
Congratulations, now you finished a whole flow to develop a component.
